PLACEHOLDER — this is NOT a real key.

The real /etc/munge/munge.key is 1024 bytes of binary randomness and is a shared
cluster secret. DO NOT commit it (.gitignore excludes the real `munge.key`).

Generate it ONCE on any machine, then base64-encode it into the cloud-init files for
every node (head + compute). All nodes must carry the byte-identical key, owned by the
munge user with mode 0400:

    dd if=/dev/urandom bs=1 count=1024 > munge.key
    chmod 400 munge.key
    base64 -w0 munge.key      # paste this string into the b64-encoded munge.key entry
                              # in deploy/cloud-init/head.yaml and compute.yaml

Common failure if keys differ or clocks drift: "Munge decode failed: Rewound credential"
or nodes stuck in DOWN/DRAIN — keep NTP/chrony running on all nodes.
